adjectives.description: disfurnished (comparative more disfurnished, superlative most disfurnished)

entries.meaning: Deprived of furniture, accoutrements or belongings; stripped, destitute.
examples: This representeth man bare and naked, acknowledging his naturall weaknesse, apt to receive from above some strange power, disfurnished of all humane knowledge […].

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of disfurnish
